## Real-World Test Results

Tests were run against an intentionally misconfigured AWS test account:

### Before Remediation

| Severity | Count | Top Findings |
|---|---|---|
| CRITICAL | 4 | Root MFA disabled, SSH open to 0.0.0.0/0, S3 public access, No CloudTrail |
| HIGH | 6 | 3 access keys never used, EBS encryption off, 2 S3 buckets unencrypted |
| MEDIUM | 8 | Password policy weak, CloudTrail log validation off, versioning disabled |
| LOW | 3 | Inline IAM policies, S3 logging disabled |

### After Remediation

| Severity | Count |
|---|---|
| CRITICAL | 0 |
| HIGH | 0 |
| MEDIUM | 1 |
| LOW | 2 |

**The scanner correctly detected every deliberately introduced misconfiguration and confirmed clean after each fix.**

