## Deploy in 5 Minutes

### Prerequisites

- AWS CLI configured (`aws configure`)
- Terraform >= 1.5 installed
- Python 3.11 installed
- A Slack webhook URL (optional but recommended)

### Steps

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/aws-cloud-security-posture-monitor
cd aws-cloud-security-posture-monitor

# 2. Set up Python environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install boto3 pytest moto black

# 3. Run tests (no AWS account needed — uses moto mocks)
pytest tests/ -v

# 4. Deploy to AWS
cd terraform
terraform init
terraform apply \
  -var="slack_webhook_url=https://hooks.slack.com/YOUR_WEBHOOK" \
  -var="alert_email=you@email.com"

# 5. Run your first scan immediately
aws lambda invoke \
  --function-name cspm-scanner \
  --payload '{}' \
  --cli-binary-format raw-in-base64-out \
  /tmp/result.json && cat /tmp/result.json | python -m json.tool
```

### Tear Down (No orphaned resources, no surprise bills)

```bash
cd terraform && terraform destroy
```

