## Roadmap

These are planned extensions that demonstrate architectural thinking:

- [ ] **Multi-account scanning** — assume IAM roles across AWS Organizations to scan all accounts from one central Lambda
- [ ] **Auto-remediation** — automatically fix LOW severity findings (enable S3 versioning, enable EBS encryption by default) with a separate Lambda triggered by findings
- [ ] **Azure module** — same framework architecture, extended to Azure using the Azure Python SDK
- [ ] **Compliance PDF report** — auto-generate a CIS compliance report as a downloadable PDF after each scan
- [ ] **Slack slash command** — `/scan` triggers an on-demand scan directly from Slack
- [ ] **JIRA integration** — automatically create JIRA tickets for CRITICAL findings with remediation steps pre-filled
- [ ] **Streamlit dashboard** — visual findings UI showing heatmaps of misconfigured resources by service and region

---

## Why This Project Matters

Cloud security is not a checkbox. It is an ongoing process of continuous monitoring, detection, and remediation. Most organisations — startups and enterprises alike — have misconfigurations sitting undetected in their AWS accounts right now. The tools to catch them exist; the gap is in operationalising them.

This project demonstrates that a single engineer with Python, Boto3, and Terraform can build a meaningful security control that runs continuously, costs almost nothing, and gives a team visibility into their real security posture — not a compliance score on a piece of paper, but actual findings on actual resources.

